06/08/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- A Turkish soldier and six Kurdish rebels were killed on Thursday (August 5th) during clashes in eastern Turkey.
The fighting erupted near Dogubayazit in the Agri province.
Members of the outlawed Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) wounded another Turkish soldier in an attack against a police station in the town of Dicle, near Diyarbakir.
In a separate incident, the Turkish military killed three suspected PKK members in a mountainous area in the Hakkari province.
Security forces also seized explosives in a car near Diyarbakir and arrested two suspected Kurdish rebels.
(Anadolu news agency, Press TV, Reuters - 05/08/10)
